HEADWORD: Throatwort
<hw>Throat"wort`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A plant (<spn>Campanula Trachelium</spn>) formerly considered a
remedy for sore throats because of its throat-shaped corolla.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Throaty</ent>⟦br⟧
